>## Priest
>*Medium humanoid (Human), any alignment*
>___
>- **Armor Class** 13 (Amor of Faith)
>- **Hit Points** 27 (5d8 + 5)
>- **Speed** 30 ft.
>___
>|STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA|
>|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|
>|10 (+0)|10 (+0)|12 (+1)|12 (+1)|14 (+2)|16 (+3)|
>___
>- **Skills** Medicine +6, Persuasion +5, Religion +5
>- **Senses** passive Perception 12
>- **Languages** any two languages
>- **Challenge** 2 (450 XP)
>- **Proficiency Bonus** +2
>___
>***Armor of Faith.*** The priest adds its charisma modifier to its armor class.  
>
>***Spellcasting.*** The priest casts one of the following spells, requiring no material components and using Charisma as the spellcasting ability (spell save DC 13):  
>
>At will: *guidance*, *light*, *resistance*  
>1/day each: *beacon of hope*, *bless*, *lesser restoration*, *revivify*, *sanctuary*  
>
>### Actions
>***Smite.*** The priest smites a creature within 60 feet that it can see with holy energies. A creature must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the target takes 18 (4d8) radiant damage, and the next weapon attack it makes deals only half as much damage.  
>
>### Bonus Actions
>***Renew (Recharge 4â€“6).*** The priest prays to the light to renew the strength of one of its comrades that it can see. A creature of its choice regains 2d4 + 3 (spell casting modifier) hit points and another 1d4 at the start of the creatures next turn.  
>If a creature is reduced to 0 hit points before its next turn it falls into a stable condition instead of dieng.

